The preview will take place on Thursday, 9 March 2017 at 19:30 for 20:00 at Ster-Kinekor cinemas in the following three cities: Rosebank in Johannesburg, Gateway in Durban and Cavendish in Cape Town. Fans need only rock up at the cinema with their copy of Nasty C s Bad Hair Extensions album to be granted a seat in the theater. Nasty C s Veliswa cinematography preview will showcase visuals of three singles off his Bad Hair Extensions album namely: Don t Do It, Phases &amp; Good Girls and Snapchat Hoes. The rapper will be in attendance at the Johannesburg Ster-Kinekor preview in Rosebank. Off the back of winning Best New Artist, Best Male Album, Best Hip Hop Album and the coveted Song Of The Year at the 16th annual Metro FM Music Awards (MMA16), Nasty C s next radio single to be released off his multi-award winning Bad Hair Extensions album is titled Uok, which is a single dedicated to his late mother Veliswa. Stream or download Uok on itunes. Brought to you by People Magazine For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.